document.contentSummary: We're finishing off the year with a recipe roundup! Flick through the gallery for our best dishes of 2017, with everything from our trending Golden Gaytime cake to quick and easy chicken ideas for the family.
document.pageMetaDescription: We're finishing the year off with a round up of our best recipes of 2017. From our top rated dinner recipes of all time, to food and cake trends, you're sure to be inspired.
document.contentBody:
[{"type":"paragraph","label":"Paragraph","content":"We're looking back on the foodie year that was - think [Golden Gaytime madness](http://www.womensweeklyfood.com.au/you-can-now-get-golden-gaytime-crumbs-in-a-tin-33065|target="_blank"), the re-emergence of old-fashioned [cob loaf recipes](http://www.womensweeklyfood.com.au/cob-loaf-recipes-34248|target="_blank") and lots of family favourites.

You'll find delicious variations on [traditional chicken curry recipes](http://www.womensweeklyfood.com.au/recipes/collections/chicken-curry-recipes|target="_blank"), new and creative ways with pasta and tasty baking ideas that deserve a place on your plates.

Flick through the gallery to relive the year in recipes, and if you haven't had a chance to make them yet, why not try them in the new year?

*Did the trend-masters get it right? Check out the [predictions for 2017 here](http://www.womensweeklyfood.com.au/food-trends-whats-coming-up-in-2017-33250|target="_blank").*"}]
